Version: 0.1.13
Date: 2026-04-13

Changes:
- Map/index orientation pipeline upgraded for practical repo onboarding:
  - semantic `Codebase Index` sections (`Directory Summary`, `Guidance Scopes`)
  - proactive guidance loading for major scopes in orientation
  - adaptive orientation/map bootstrap budgets based on repository size
- Runtime map maintenance improved:
  - automatic progress snapshot updates from runtime signals
  - potential stale-guidance detection when code changes outpace local map updates
- Progress noise reduced:
  when commit signal is present, auto-progress now writes only the commit line
  (no redundant changed-files line in the same event).
- Test and lifecycle coverage expanded:
  - added dedicated map lifecycle E2E scenarios (semantic index, generated scopes,
    commit/no-commit progress behavior, guidance staleness, git-note attachment)
  - updated orientation budget expectations for small repositories.

Related commits:
- feat(context): harden map/index orientation and auto-progress pipeline
- fix(context): tighten progress auto-lines and map lifecycle assertions for release
